EnExplanation: The word 'olnud' is the past participle of 'olema', which means 'to be' in Estonian. It indicates a state of having existed or occurred in the past.

Samples.EeSentence: Ma olen olnud seal juba mitu korda.
Samples.EnSentence: I have been there many times.

Samples.EeSentence: Ta on selline inimene, kes on alati olnud abivalmis.
Samples.EnSentence: He is the kind of person who has always been helpful.
